            . I am the wife of Thomas Mellows - he lives in St. Ann's-court, and <rs id="t18260406-125-viclabel659" type="occupation">deals in books</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260406-125-victim726 t18260406-125-viclabel659"></join>. - On the 1st of April I saw the prisoner near the house - I was cleaning in the back parlour, which is dark, and suppose he did not see me; he came into the shop, took a book, and went out with it - I ran after him, and he turned into Richmond-buildings, where I caught him, and gave charge of him - he threw the book down, and a carter, who was passing, took it up.</p>
